data.content:
noun
or fte , pl fetes
[count] US :a large party or celebration
Brit :an outdoor event for raising money that usually includes competitions and things for sale
won a prize at the church/village fete
verb
or fte fetes or ftes; feted or fted; feting or fting
[+ obj] :to honor (a person) or celebrate (something) with a large party or public celebration
They feted the winning team with banquets and parades. - often used as (be) feted
She was feted for her contributions to science.
